data.title: Washington Cities by Population (2024)
data.meta_description: Get a list of Washington cities by population based on Census 2023 data.
data.text:
The most populated cities in Washington are Seattle with 755,078, Spokane at 229,447, Tacoma with 222,906, Vancouver at 196,442, and Bellevue with 151,574. You can get the most current Census population data for all 635 Washington cities, sorted from the most populous cities in Washington to the least, according to the 2023 Population Estimates Program and 2022 American Community Survey.
